{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"483264d0-1b7f-42f3-ab85-4872c7d3e579","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n\n// For Theory:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest(int x) { }\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\npublic void MyTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report skipped tests in results with the reason message visible in test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"599a5053-bfa2-4011-a733-788db71eaebf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":263,"requestId":"0C02:A917E:53BBF6:620A2E:69F009AF"},"id":"c8d2c1f7-2784-4f93-a6c6-7159fc4a4e68","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:13:25.353Z","parentId":"9a0f5fd4-7883-4af0-99ed-c42aa08f5843"}
